<item>
            <title>[HADOOP-2776] Web interface uses internal hostnames on EC2</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HADOOP-2776</link>
                <project id="12310240" key="HADOOP">Hadoop Common</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The web interface, for example &lt;a href=&quot;http://$MASTER_HOST:50030/machines.jsp&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://$MASTER_HOST:50030/machines.jsp&lt;/a&gt;, uses internal hostnames when running on EC2.  This makes it impossible to access from outside EC2.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The slaves file has the public names listed.  Resolving a public name inside EC2 returns the private IP (which would reverse to the internal DNS name).&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;EC2 ami-a324c1ca&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
